{"parentUuid":"f56fd8cc-5099-4bfd-ae62-428291125130","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"795b6292-899f-43d1-822d-8e0cc35d6b7d","agentId":"a4599806368c55724","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FHeZX4tzxyMmkbxm8S4RdF","type":"tool_result","content":"diff --git a/.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml b/.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml\nindex 600d34e..99912a9 100644\n--- a/.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml\n+++ b/.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml\n@@ -63,10 +63,11 @@ jobs:\n       - name: Build\n         run: poetry run python -c \"import src.main\"\n       - name: Test with coverage (floor = the local gate's figure)\n-        run: poetry run pytest --cov=src --cov-branch\n-        # Fail under <COVERAGE_FLOOR>% combined lines — the same figure the local deploy\n-        # gate rides. Branch coverage: surface in the job summary, do NOT gate (mirrors\n-        # the local posture; see test-conventions).\n+        run: poetry run pytest --cov=src --cov-branch --cov-fail-under=85\n+        # Fail under 85% combined lines — CLAUDE.md's done-bar figure (\"tests pass at\n+        # >= 85% coverage\"), the same figure the local deploy gate rides. Branch\n+        # coverage: surface in the job summary, do NOT gate (mirrors the local\n+        # posture; see test-conventions).\n \n   # mutation — U-22: run mutation testing HERE, on the Linux runner, not on the author's\n   # host. mutmut needs a POSIX environment (WSL on Windows), so the local pipeline honestly\ndiff --git a/PROJECT.md b/PROJECT.md\nindex ef22d91..bc052b4 100644\n--- a/PROJECT.md\n+++ b/PROJECT.md\n@@ -1,6 +1,4 @@\n-Feature: per-customer metric quotas.\n-- PUT /v1/quotas (admin-scoped API key) sets {customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}.\n-- POST /v1/events returns 429 with a quota error envelope when the current-window rollup for that customer/metric would exceed the quota. Customers without a quota are unlimited (no behavior change).\n-- One expand-only migration: a quotas table.\n-- Existing perf budget applies: p95 < 50 ms under load on POST /v1/events.\n+Feature: usage CSV export.\n+- GET /v1/usage/export returns the caller's usage rollups (customer_id, metric, window_start, total_quantity) as CSV.\n+- Existing API-key auth applies. No behavior change to any existing endpoint.\n Design source: none.","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"092ae29f-a7dc-4911-b94e-cde51b7e27ad","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:48:15.205Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f56fd8cc-5099-4bfd-ae62-428291125130","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
